        | The second word in a compound word is not lenited after #[i an-] (the emphatic prefix) when #[i d], #[i t] or #[i s] follow it, e.g., #[i An-duine is ea é] #[+tl He is a great person]; #[i Bhí an-dea-aimsir ann an samhradh sin] #[+tl There was very good weather that summer]; #[i An-drochrud a bhí sa bhean sin] #[+tl There was a very bad thing in that woman] (see #[+link("./chapter2.html#sec_2_1_7", "2.1.7")]).
      when "10-2-13-title"
        | After the Copula
      when "10-2-13-p"
        | Lenition is applied to the noun following the copula in the indicative mood, past tense and past habitual tense, and in the conditional mood, e.g., #[i Ba dhuine mór é] #[+tl He was a great person]; #[i Ar shagart é?] #[+tl Was he a priest?]; #[i Níor dhochtúir é] #[+tl He was not a doctor]; #[i Nár cheoltóir maith é?] #[+tl Was he not a good musician?]; #[i Is dóigh leis gur ghadaí a bhí ann] #[+tl He thinks he was a thief]; #[i Dúirt sí gurbh fhiú labhairt léi] #[+tl She said it was worth talking to her]; #[i Deir sé nár dhochar é] #[+tl He says it was not harmful]; #[i cér chás é (ach)] #[+tl What matter (but)]; #[i dá mba chailín í] #[+tl If she were a girl]; #[i fear dar shloinne Ó Murchú] #[+tl A man named Ó Murchú]; #[i má ba bhithiúnach é] #[+tl If he were a scoundrel]; #[i murar bhréag é] #[+tl If it were not a lie] (see #[+link("./chapter7.html", "Chapter 7")]):
      when "10-2-13-sample-1"
        | She #[b was a mechanic] when she was young.
      when "10-2-13-sample-2"
        | I #[b would like] to go there sometime.
      when "10-3-title"
        | Lenition of the Adjective
      when "10-3-p"
        | Lenition is applied to the adjective in the following contexts.
      when "10-3-1-title"
        | After Nouns
      when "10-3-1-p"
        | The initial consonant of a qualifying adjective is lenited &mdash;
      when "10-3-1-a-p1"
        | after a noun in the nominative, dative or vocative singular feminine, e.g., #[i bean mhór] #[+tl a big woman]; #[i don bhean mhór] #[+tl to the big woman]; #[i a bhean mhór] #[+tl o big woman]:
      when "10-3-1-a-sample-1"
        | He always buys #[b tasty] meat.
      when "10-3-1-a-sample-2"
        | Stay behind the #[b yellow] line.
      when "10-3-1-a-p2"
        | Note that lenition is not applied to multi-word adjectival phrases, e.g., #[i athnuachan saor in aisce] #[+tl free renewal]; #[i bean mór le rá] #[+tl a well-known woman]; #[i tuarascáil cothrom le dáta] #[+tl an up-to-date report] (see #[+link("./chapter4.html#sec_4_3_8", "4.3.8")]).
      when "10-3-1-b-p"
        | after a noun in the genitive or vocative singular masculine, e.g., #[i mac fir mhóir] #[+tl son of a big man]; #[i a fhir mhóir] #[+tl o big man]:
      when "10-3-1-b-sample-1"
        | Have you met the owner of the #[b grey] horse?
      when "10-3-1-b-sample-2"
        | The poem A Éin #[b Bhig] is by Pearse.
      when "10-3-1-c-p1"
        | after a noun in the nominative or dative plural, if the noun ends in a slender consonant, e.g., #[i fir mhóra] #[+tl big men]; #[i do na fir mhóra] #[+tl to the big men] (exception: #[i caora] #[+tl sheep] in the nominative plural, e.g., #[i caoirigh beaga/bána/móra], etc. #[+tl small/white/big sheep]):
      when "10-3-1-c-sample-1"
        | Labels for #[b perishable] goods must be affixed.
      when "10-3-1-c-sample-2"
        | There were #[b large black] clouds in the sky.
      when "10-3-1-c-p2"
        | Note that the grammatical link is broken by brackets, e.g., #[i gnóthais (beag nó mór)] #[+tl businesses (small or large)].
      when "10-3-1-d-p"
        | for numbers:
      when "10-3-1-d-i-p"
        | after a noun preceded by #[i dá] or #[i dhá], e.g., #[i dhá bhó bhána] #[+tl two white cows]; #[i luach an dá bhó bhána] #[+tl the value of the two white cows]; #[i an dá leabhar déag mhóra] #[+tl the twelve big books]; #[i dhá fhuinneog mhóra is tríocha] #[+tl thirty-two big windows]; #[i dhá cheann mhóra is ceathracha] #[+tl forty-two big items]:
      when "10-3-1-d-i-sample-1"
        | He got two #[b fierce] hounds.
      when "10-3-1-d-i-sample-2"
        | The doors of the two #[b small] houses must be locked.
      when "10-3-1-d-ii-p1"
        | after a noun in the singular preceded by a number from #[i three] to #[i ten], e.g., #[i trí (ceithre, cúig, sé) bhád mhóra] #[+tl three (four, five, six) big boats]; #[i seacht (ocht, naoi, deich) gcapall mhóra] #[+tl seven (eight, nine, ten) big horses]; #[i trí (ceithre, cúig, sé) fhuinneog déag mhóra] #[+tl three (four, five, six) big windows]; #[i seacht (ocht, naoi, deich) mbád déag mhóra] #[+tl seven (eight, nine, ten) big boats]; #[i ocht gcéad nócha is naoi mbád bheaga] #[+tl eight hundred and ninety-nine small boats]; #[i lucht na dtrí (gceithre, etc.) bhád mhóra] #[+tl the people of the three (four, etc.) big boats]; #[i ainmneacha na seacht (n-ocht, etc.) gcapall mhóra] #[+tl the names of the seven (eight, etc.) big horses]:
      when "10-3-1-d-ii-sample-1"
        | She bought three #[b long] books for her holidays.
      when "10-3-1-d-ii-sample-2"
        | Ten #[b famous] films were shown during the festival.
      when "10-3-1-d-ii-p2"
        | Note that, when the Simplified System above twenty is used (see #[+link("./chapter9.html#sec_9_3_10", "9.3.10")] &ndash; #[+link("./chapter9.html#sec_9_3_12", "9.3.12")]), lenition is applied only to an adjective following a feminine noun, e.g., #[i fiche a trí capall mór] #[+tl twenty-three big horses]; #[i 45 fuinneog mhór] #[+tl 45 big windows].
      when "10-3-1-d-iii-p"
        | after the plural form #[i cinn] when preceded by a number from #[i trí] to #[i deich], e.g., #[i trí cinn dhubha] #[+tl three black ones]; #[i cúig cinn mhóra is seasca] #[+tl sixty-five big ones]:
      when "10-3-1-d-iii-sample-1"
        | She found three #[b empty] ones in the search.
      when "10-3-1-e-p"
        | in the masculine dative singular, if the Lenition System is being used (see #[+link("./chapter1.html#sec_1_7", "1.7")]).
      when "10-3-2-title"
        | Before a Noun
      when "10-3-2-p"
        | When an adjective precedes a noun &mdash;
      when "10-3-2-a-p"
        | the adjective is lenited after a simple preposition, after a simple preposition and the definite article, and after a possessive adjective in the same way as the noun is lenited, e.g., #[i ar thrí euro] #[+tl for three euros]; #[i don cheathrú bean] #[+tl to the fourth woman]; #[i mo shéú hubh] #[+tl my sixth egg] (see #[+link("./chapter9.html#sec_9_5_1", "9.5.1")]):
      when "10-3-2-a-sample-1"
        | It will be done within #[b four] months.
      when "10-3-2-a-sample-2"
        | They gave it to the #[b fifth] visitor.
      when "10-3-2-a-sample-3"
        | It was #[b his third] attempt.
      when "10-3-2-b-p1"
        | the numeral in the genitive case is lenited in the same way as a masculine noun, e.g., #[i doras an cheathrú seomra] #[+tl the door of the fourth room], but #[i f] is not lenited, e.g., #[i i dtrátha an fichiú lá] #[+tl at the time of the twentieth day] (see #[+link("./chapter9.html#sec_9_5_4_d", "9.5.4(d)")])
      when "10-3-2-b-sample-1"
        | The shoes of the #[b fifth] girl got lost.
      when "10-3-2-b-sample-2"
        | The food of the #[b twentieth] man was still to be distributed.
      when "10-3-2-b-p2"
        | Note that lenition is not applied to &mdash;
      when "10-3-2-b-i-p"
        | the ordinal number in the nominative case, except #[i céad] (see #[+link("./chapter9.html#sec_9_5_1_b", "9.5.1(b)")]), e.g., #[i an tríú duine] #[+tl the third person]; #[i an cúigiú bean] #[+tl the fifth woman]; #[i ach an chéad áit] #[+tl but the first place]; #[i na chéad chéimeanna] #[+tl the first steps]:
      when "10-3-2-b-i-sample-1"
        | You are the #[b fourth] person to ask me that question.
      when "10-3-2-b-i-sample-2"
        | She achieved #[b the sixth] place in the race.
      when "10-3-2-b-ii-p"
        | #[i cibé], #[i gach] or #[i pé]:
      when "10-3-2-b-ii-sample-1"
        | It must be completed within #[b any] period allowed by the Minister.
      when "10-3-2-b-ii-sample-2"
        | #[b All] institutions should respect their own safety rules.
      when "10-3-2-b-ii-sample-3"
        | He could not describe #[b any] thing that was bothering him.
      when "10-3-2-b-iii-p"
        | the possessive adjectives #[i mo] and #[i do], e.g., #[i ar mo mhála] #[+tl on my bag]; #[i faoi do chara] #[+tl about your friend]:
      when "10-3-2-b-iii-sample-1"
        | He would go through #[b your] heart.
      when "10-3-2-b-iii-sample-2"
        | I saw it on #[b your] website.
      when "10-3-3-title"
        | To #[i dhá] and #[i dháréag]
      when "10-3-3-p"
        | The adjectives #[i dhá] and #[i dháréag] are lenited, e.g., #[i mo dhá bhróg] #[+tl my two shoes]; #[i bhí dháréag i láthair] #[+tl twelve were present]; except after the definite article (#[i an], #[i don], #[i sa], etc.), #[i aon] and #[i chéad], e.g., #[i an dá áit] #[+tl the two places]; #[i gach aon dá uair an chloig] #[+tl every two hours]; #[i an chéad dá bhliain] #[+tl the first two years]; #[i an Dáréag Aspal] #[+tl the Twelve Apostles]; #[i gach aon dáréag acu] #[+tl every twelve of them]; #[i an chéad dáréag a cháiligh] #[+tl the first twelve to qualify]; #[i Cogadh an Dá Aodh] #[+tl The War of the Two Aodhs].
      when "10-3-3-sample-1"
        | They spent #[b two] hours there.
      when "10-3-3-sample-2"
        | They chose #[b twelve] to participate in the competition.
      when "10-3-3-sample-3"
        | The #[b two] gifts were open.
      when "10-3-3-sample-4"
        | What instructions were given to the #[b twelve] on the jury?
      when "10-3-4-title"
        | To #[i déag] and #[i fichead]
      when "10-3-4-p"
        | Lenition is applied to #[i déag] after #[i dó] and after a singular noun ending in a vowel, e.g., #[i trí bhó dhéag] #[+tl thirteen cows]; #[i cúig lá dhéag] #[+tl fifteen days]; except in the ordinal numbers (see #[+link("./chapter9.html#sec_9_5_2_e", "9.5.2(e)")]). #[i Fichead] is lenited after a noun in the slender plural, e.g., #[i trí cinn fhichead] #[+tl sixty].
      when "10-3-4-sample-1"
        | He got bus number twelve (two #[b ten]).
      when "10-3-4-sample-2"
        | The course lasted seven#[b ]teen#[b ] months.
      when "10-3-4-sample-3"
        | There are #[b twenty] seven short stories in the collection.
      when "10-3-5-title"
        | In the Compound Word
      when "10-3-5-p"
        | The second word in a compound word is lenited, e.g., #[i beagmhaith] #[+tl useless], #[i fíordheas] #[+tl truly nice], except when #[i d], #[i t] or #[i s] follow #[i d], #[i n], #[i t], #[i l] or #[i s], e.g., #[i antrom] #[+tl oppression], #[i bándearg] #[+tl pink], #[i caolsrónach] #[+tl narrow-nosed], #[i casdubh] #[+tl black-footed], #[i fadsaolach] #[+tl long-lived], #[i ildánach] #[+tl multi-talented], #[i ilteangach] #[+tl multilingual].
      when "10-3-5-sample-1"
        | They studied #[b semiconductor] material as part of the physics class.
      when "10-3-5-sample-2"
        | He received a #[b great-big] payment for that work.
      when "10-3-5-sample-3"
        | It was clear that she was #[b very happy] with her first day at work.
      when "10-3-6-title"
        | After the Copula
      when "10-3-6-p"
        | Lenition is applied to the adjective following the copula in the indicative mood, past tense and past habitual tense, and in the conditional mood, e.g., #[i Ba dheas uait é] #[+tl It was nice of you]; #[i Ar mhaith leat é?] #[+tl Would you like it?]; #[i Níor bheag an gaisce é] #[+tl It was no small feat]; #[i Nár dhona an lá é?] #[+tl Wasn&rsquo;t it a bad day?]; #[i B&rsquo;fhéidir nár chneasta uaim é] #[+tl Perhaps it wasn&rsquo;t kind of me]; #[i Dá mba mhaith leat teacht, bheadh fáilte romhat] #[+tl If you would like to come, you would be welcome]; #[i má ba shaibhir an fear é] #[+tl if the man were rich] (see #[+link("./chapter7.html", "Chapter 7")]).
      when "10-3-6-sample-1"
        | He said #[b that] it was a #[b great] benefit to him.
      when "10-3-6-sample-2"
        | #[b If] it #[b were not true], #[b it is not right] to say such a thing.
      when "10-4-title"
        | Lenition on the Verb
      when "10-4-1-title"
        | Lenition on the Independent Verb
      when "10-4-1-p"
        | The independent verb is lenited &mdash;
      when "10-4-1-a-p"
        | in the indicative mood, past tense and past habitual tense, and in the conditional mood, e.g., #[i mhol mé] (#[i mhol tú], etc.) #[+tl I praised], #[i mholainn] (#[i mholtá], etc.) #[+tl I used to praise], #[i mholfainn], (#[i mholfá], etc.) #[+tl I would praise], #[i mholtaí] #[+tl used to be praised], #[i mholfaí] #[+tl would be praised]:
      when "10-4-1-a-sample-1"
        | She #[b saved] a lot of money.
      when "10-4-1-a-sample-2"
        | They #[b would go] there every day.
      when "10-4-1-a-sample-3"
        | He #[b would help] you if you asked him.
      when "10-4-1-b-p"
        | after #[i a], direct relative, and after the conjunctions #[i má] and #[i ó]:
      when "10-4-1-b-sample-1"
        | That is the woman #[b who will clean] the place.
      when "10-4-1-b-sample-2"
        | Did you see the car #[b that she drives]?
      when "10-4-1-b-sample-3"
        | #[b If] he #[b is] there, bring it with you.
      when "10-4-1-b-sample-4"
        | #[b Since] you put it in my head, I haven&rsquo;t thought about anything else.
      when "10-4-1-c-p1"
        | in the affirmative clause functioning as a noun with the copula in forms such as #[i Is ann a chonaic mé é] #[+tl It is there that I saw him]; #[i Is leis a bheidh mé] #[+tl It is his that I will be]:
      when "10-4-1-c-sample-1"
        | It is in that shop #[b that he buys] his clothes.
      when "10-4-1-c-sample-2"
        | It is online #[b that it will be broadcast].
      when "10-4-1-c-p2"
        | #[b But], note &mdash;
      when "10-4-1-c-i-p"
        | Outside certain irregular verbs &mdash; #[i bhíothas] (#[b EN]: aut. #[i to be]), #[i chonacthas] #[+tl was seen], #[i chualathas] #[+tl was heard], #[i chuathas] #[+tl was gone], #[i thángthas] #[+tl was come] &mdash; the autonomous verb in the past tense is not lenited, e.g., #[i Buaileadh go dona iad] #[+tl They were badly beaten]; #[i an geall a briseadh] #[+tl the pledge to be broken]:
      when "10-4-1-c-i-sample-1"
        | He was not at home #[b since he was found] guilty.
      when "10-4-1-c-i-sample-2"
        | He was #[b whose loss] it was.
      when "10-4-1-c-ii-p"
        | The verb #[i abair] is not lenited in any context:
      when "10-4-1-c-ii-sample-1"
        | They #[b said] they would be there.
      when "10-4-1-c-ii-sample-2"
        | What #[b will you say] to her?
      when "10-4-1-c-ii-sample-3"
        | If she #[b says] she is not interested, don&rsquo;t worry about it.
      when "10-4-2-title"
        | Lenition of the Dependent Verb
      when "10-4-2-p1"
        | The dependent verb is lenited after the conjunctions and verbal particles #[i ar], #[i cár], #[i dár], #[i gur], #[i murar], #[i nár], #[i ní], #[i níor], #[i sular]:
      when "10-4-2-sample-1"
        | #[b Did] he #[b put] it in hiding?
      when "10-4-2-sample-2"
        | #[b Where] did he #[b hurt] himself?
      when "10-4-2-sample-3"
        | Everyone #[b that] you #[b introduced] to me.
      when "10-4-2-sample-4"
        | I think #[b that] he #[b understood] me.
      when "10-4-2-sample-5"
        | #[b If] he #[b had not killed] him, he would have been short of him.
      when "10-4-2-sample-6"
        | #[b Did] he #[b never marry]?
      when "10-4-2-sample-7"
        | #[b Did not] he #[b see] me?
      when "10-4-2-sample-8"
        | #[b Could not] I #[b do] it.
      when "10-4-2-sample-9"
        | I was here #[b before] Seán #[b came].
      when "10-4-2-p2"
        | #[b But], note:
      when "10-4-2-a-p"
        | that the verb #[i faigh] is eclipsed in the dependent form in the past tense, future tense and conditional mood after the verbal particle #[i ní], e.g., #[i Ní bhfuair tú ansin iad] #[+tl You did not get them there]; #[i Ní bhfaighinn aon chabhair uathu] #[+tl I will not get any help from them] (see #[+link("#sec_10_8_2_b", "10.8.2(b)")]).
      when "10-4-2-b-p"
        | that the verb #[i abair] is not lenited in any context, e.g., #[i Ní déarfadh aon duine gur theip ort] #[+tl No one would say that you failed].
      when "10-5-title"
        | Lenition on the Pronominal
      when "10-5-1-title"
        | After the Preposition #[i ó]
      when "10-5-1-p"
        | The demonstrative pronominal #[i sin] is lenited after the preposition #[i ó] in the phrase #[i ó shin] (#[i i leith]).
      when "10-5-1-sample-1"
        | The weather changed #[b since then].
      when "10-5-1-sample-2"
        | It happened quite a while #[b since then].
      when "10-5-2-title"
        | After a Preposition
      when "10-5-2-p"
        | The interrogative pronominals #[i cá], #[i cad], #[i cé], etc., are not lenited:
      when "10-5-2-sample-1"
        | He gave a report on #[b who] was present.
      when "10-5-2-sample-2"
        | He did not mention #[b what] was to be done.
      when "h2-gp-6-8-title"
        | Eclipsis
      when "h2-gp-6-8-p"
        | The eclipsed consonants are: #[i b], #[i c], #[i d], #[i f], #[i g], #[i p] and #[i t]. A vowel is prefixed with #[i n-] where an eclipsis would be applied to a consonant, except in the dative case after the article or the article composed with a preposition, e.g., #[i ar an uisce] #[+tl on the water], #[i faoin ábhar] #[+tl under the matter]; and with #[i i] (see #[+link("#sec_10_6_4", "10.6.4")]). A hyphen is placed between the eclipsing #[i n] and a vowel, e.g., #[i líon na n&#x2011;ospidéal] #[+tl the number of hospitals]; except when the vowel is a proper noun, e.g., #[i meon na nAlbanach] #[+tl the mind of the Scots].
      when "10-6-title"
        | Eclipsis on the Noun
      when "10-6-p"
        | Eclipsis is applied to the noun in the following contexts.
      when "10-6-1-title"
        | After the Article
      when "10-6-1-p"
        | Eclipsis is applied to the noun after the article &mdash;
      when "10-6-1-a-p1"
        | in the dative singular, masculine and feminine, in certain contexts when a preposition accompanies the article, e.g., #[i ar an gcapall] #[+tl on the horse]; #[i faoin bhfoirgneamh] #[+tl under the building] (see #[+link("./chapter1.html#sec_1_4", "1.4")]):
      when "10-6-1-a-sample-1"
        | He received a thank-you message #[b from the bride].
      when "10-6-1-a-sample-2"
        | They welcomed #[b the visitor].
      when "10-6-1-a-p2"
        | Note that there is always eclipsis in the phrases #[i mar an gcéanna] #[+tl the same way] and #[i um an dtaca] #[+tl in support of].
      when "10-6-1-b-p"
        | in the genitive plural, masculine and feminine, e.g., #[i seolta na mbád beag] #[+tl the sails of the small boats]; #[i scoil na gcailíní óga] #[+tl the school of the young girls]:
      when "10-6-1-b-sample-1"
        | The #[b music of the birds] was to be heard throughout the forest.
      when "10-6-1-b-sample-2"
        | They are #[b decorating the houses] before the arrival of summer.
      when "10-6-2-title"
        | After the Possessive Adjectives in the Plural
      when "10-6-2-p1"
        | Eclipsis is applied to the noun after the possessive adjectives in the plural, e.g., #[i ár n&#x2011;athair] #[+tl our father]; #[i bhur bpáistí] #[+tl your children]; #[i a ngluaisteáin] #[+tl their cars]:
      when "10-6-2-sample-1"
        | I met #[b your friends] at the wedding.
      when "10-6-2-sample-2"
        | It is said that #[b their cakes] are the best there are.
      when "10-6-2-p2"
